  "time_ut": 1656912586,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7\u0dda \u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d87\u0dc4\u0dd0\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The President of the country is not visible",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Member of Parliament Wimal Wirawamsa said that the nation is suffering from a serious problem and the President of the country is not even in sight. He said this while speaking in Parliament today (04th).",
        "\"Today, we are meeting the parliament under not normal conditions. There is a situation where the people of the country have imposed a self-imposed curfew without fuel. There are kilometers long queues of vehicles near the IOC Shed.",
        "Even the MPs are nervous about how they will get there if they go on a journey. The Prime Minister is not in the House today. Energy Minister no. What do you say to the public affected by this crisis?",
        "There is a president of the country that cannot be seen. Not visible to the public. People are in very serious pain. There is no hope of relief for the people.",
        "There is no confidence in the international community about this regime. There is no such thing as international confidence that Ranil was appointed. He is a single MP from the national list who lost by a vote. The international community will not believe that such a person became the prime minister.",
        "Please, let's get these parties together and form an all-party government. Let's make a work order to win the trust of the country and the international trust. We're sitting on top of a volcano and playing tennis.\""
      ],
